Blocks.childText: 476 CROSS AND COMFORT. Dark lies and sore temptations Lord, hear my prayers, And break these snares And hellish machinations. 6 With Thee, Lord, would I cast my lot ; _My God, my God, forsake me not, For, Lord, I am commending My soul to Thee; Deliver me Now, and when life is ending. by All honor, praise, and majesty To Father, Son, and Spirit be, Our God forever glorious, In whose rich grace We'll run our race, Till we depart victorious. 353 S. M. IN weariness and pain, By sins and fears oppressed, I turn me to my Rest again, My soul's eternal Rest: 2 The Lamb that died for me, And still my load doth bear; To Jesus' streaming wounds I flee, And find my quiet there;
